value.Directions: Co Rd 82 W Left on Town Hall Road to Rockbury lots, turn on Faith Hill Dr.
value.PublicRemarks: Dreaming of building a home.  Rockbury lots, unique views throughout the development and a park for the kids.  Tar roads, city sewer, large lots close to many lakes and recreation.  Close to Lake Latoka Beach.  The lots are .50 - .75 acres and Alexandria is only 3.5 miles away.  Curb and gutter.  All assessments paid.  $60.00 association fee a year.

value.Directions: HWY 212 TO CO RD 11, NORTH TO CHASKA BLVD, EAST TO PROPERTY
value.PublicRemarks: WONDERFUL 103.43+/- ACRES RIGHT IN THE CITY OF CHASKA, NEAR FUTURE SCHOOL SITE, LARGE OAK & MAPLE FOREST, GREAT LAND FOR FUTURE HOUSING DEVELOPMENT, CONTRACT FOR DEED TERMS AVAILABLE TO MAKE IT AFFORDABLE NOW AND PLAN AHEAD FOR A BEAUTIFUL FUTURE.

value.Directions: I-35 to Rush City exit.  East 1/2 mile to Fairfield Ave. Turn left and go approx. 4 miles to property on the right.
value.PublicRemarks: 789 acres. 1.5 miles of road frontage on Interstate 35.  Approx. 90,000 sq ft of out buildings. 1 (400x100) feeder barn, permit for 1,000 head feeder lot.  3 wells.  300 ft of railroad frontage.  All level ground.  No equipment included.  3 bedroom home included on property.

value.Directions: exit 32 onto county hwy-52, turn right onto 95th ave ne, turn right onto 101st ave ne
value.PublicRemarks: Located in high demand Blaine area close to Blaine Brothers in Blaine minutes to 35W. Just north of the Pet Lodge, high traffic count daily over 19,000. Property is Zoned Light Industrial. 12.26 Acres with Approx 5 to 6 are Buildable the rest are wetlands that would have to be filled and you would need to follow steps requirements with the city and you would need to get approval to do that. This is also a Corner Lot

value.Directions: Highway 36 to Stillwater Blvd (Hwy 5), head South to 50th St. N., head West on 50th St. N., Property on North side of Road
value.PublicRemarks: 110 Acres in PRIME Lake Elmo; land abuts and access through the Luxury Sanctuary Development.  Land is also accessible from 50th St. N. (off Stillwater Blvd.-Hwy 5).  Proposing 50 lot subdivision to city of Lake Elmo; would be a Luxury open space development with lots starting at $225,000.  The land features several high quality wetlands, an oak savana, a tamarack tree island, beautiful vistas and rolling topography.  Minutes from Oak park Heights/Stillwater shopping, downtown Stillwater, Highway 36 and 694.  Great Stillwater schools with close proximity to the high school.

value.Directions: Exit I-94 to Exit 100 then Hwy 27 towards town .5 miles to a right on Nevada to left and sign on 42nd Ave.
value.PublicRemarks: Two lots located in Industrial Park next to I-94 totaling 1.53 acres and ideal for new development.  Easy access with Exit 103 to the east and Exit 100 less than a mile to the west.

value.Directions: From Willmar take Hwy 12 E for 13 miles to Atwater. Once in Atwater go past the gas station & the lot is on the North-side
value.PublicRemarks: Nice large lot with the option to build a new home, storage shed or garage.  City parks, library, baseball fields and school all within walking distance.
